[Claude]: Now I have the complete picture. Let me submit the findings.

**Key vulnerability confirmed**: In `doCheckScriptCompile` at line 143:
```java
new CpsGroovyShellFactory(null).withParent(trusted).withSandbox(true).build().getClassLoader().parseClass(value);
```

This calls `getClassLoader().parseClass(value)` directly on the `GroovyClassLoader` (which is `CleanGroovyClassLoader`), **bypassing the `CpsGroovyShell.parse()` method** which calls `doParse()` which sets up the `GroovySandbox.Scope`. The sandbox interceptor is NOT active during this `parseClass` call, so:

1. Groovy AST transforms annotated with `@GroovyASTTransformation` can execute code at compile time
2. The `@Grab` annotation (Grape dependency manager) can execute code at compile time
3. Static initializers may execute on class loading

This is a **sandbox bypass** where a user with `Job.CONFIGURE` can execute arbitrary code on the Jenkins controller without script approval.

For `doCheckScriptCompile` in `ReplayAction.java` (line 356-357), it simply delegates to `CpsFlowDefinition.DescriptorImpl.doCheckScriptCompile`, so the same vulnerability applies there too.

